#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<'EOF'
NovaArch first boot notes
------------------------
- Logitech G HUB is not available on Linux; use piper/solaar/openrgb alternatives.
- For Logitech wheel tuning, try oversteer.
- Lian Li SL Wireless LCD Linux control may be partial/unofficial.
- USB live session logs in automatically as live. Use Welcome → Launch Installer (guided archinstall): connect Wi‑Fi first, then set timezone/disks/account in that wizard after it opens. Two monitors: Super+[ / Super+] switches focus between screens (Control Center → Display shortcuts too).
- Choose animated scene with: novaarch-wallpaper-selector
- Update indicator appears in Waybar as "UPD <count>".
- NovaArch Control Center opens on login (toggle inside it if you want to disable).
- Shortcut: SUPER+SHIFT+C opens Control Center.
- NovaArch Welcome app opens on login (toggle inside it if you want to disable).
- Shortcut: SUPER+SHIFT+A opens Welcome app.
- If Bluetooth/Wi-Fi need reset: sudo novaarch-wireless-repair
EOF
